  • FOR USE WITH MODERN FORMS SMART FANS ONLY! A wall control or remote control is included with every Modern Forms Smart Fan, check product details to confirm control type included. Modern Forms Smart Fans can also be controlled through the Modern Forms App on any iOS or Android device.
  • Modern Forms controls are manufactured in RF or Bluetooth versions and are not cross compatible with each other - please make sure to order the correct version based on your ceiling fan. Bluetooth controls ship with all current models and RF controls are for older models purchased prior to 2021. To confirm your control version, please check the part number on the label of your control.
  • Up to 8 Modern Forms Remote Controls can be added to any Modern Forms Smart Fan (two or more controls for one fan or a group of fans).
  • Control features a Luminaire on/off button and 0-100% brightness control buttons with a fan on/off button and 6 speed fan control up/down buttons with a Winter/Summer mode button to reverse your fan for warm or cool air flow.
  • UL & cUL Damp Location Listed for indoor or covered applications.

Customer ratings by feature

Additional details

Battery operated bluetooth wireless remote for fan control. Wireless remote is optional - each Modern Forms Ceiling Fan can be controlled through the free Modern Forms App available in the Google Play or App Store. Battery operated (CR 2032 battery included), lasts up to 5-years with normal use. Luminaire on/off control and 0-100% brightness control with fan on/off button and 6 speed fan control. Includes Winter/Summer mode switch to reverse fan for warm or cool air flow. Includes a magnetic cradle with easy installation for wall mounting. Touch panel wall control with Modern Forms Fan App can be purchased separately (Part# F-TS-BK or -WT).

  • Most Modern Forms Smart Fans come with a Bluetooth Remote Control with Wall Cradle in the box
  • Up to 8 Modern Forms Remote Controls can be added to any Modern Forms Smart Fan (two or more controls for one fan or a group of fans)


Remote Control

The Bluetooth enabled remote control with magnetic wall cradle and can be paired with an unlimited amount of Modern Forms Smart Fans within range, operating from up to 100ft away. Optional Bluetooth Hardwired Wall Control can be purchased separately (Part # F-WCBT-WT).

Remote control functions include:

  • Fan On/Off
  • Fan Speed Up/Down (6-Speeds) with Audible Beep Confirmation of Speed Change
  • Light On/Off
  • Light Dim Up/Down
  • Fan Mode Toggle Modes (Winter/Summer)


Advanced Control

All Modern Forms Smart Fans can be controlled by most iPhone or Android devices. No additional hardware or purchases are necessary other than your iPhone or Android device. The app is available for download free through the iPhone App Store or Google Play Stores.

App functions include all of the basic Remote Control Features Plus:

  • 7/365 Day Scheduling
  • Adaptive Learning
  • Fan Grouping
  • Advanced Smart Home Integration


Smart Control

All Modern Forms Smart Fans can be controlled with the Smart Home Tech you know and love: Amazon Alexa, Google Home, Samsung SmartThings, and Ecobee. Smart Home Integration is a cinch - simply download the Modern Forms App on your iOS or Android device and follow the integration steps.

Smart Home Integration Includes:

  • Amazon Alexa
  • Google Home Assistant
  • Samsung SmartThings
  • Ecobee Thermostat
  • Control 4 / Josh AI

Coming soon through app updates: Savant, Lutron Homeworks, and Nest.

      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      A little trick I learned
      Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2022
      Style: Contemporary
      This is not listen anywhere in their documentation, but the “power out” wire does not need to be used. I did not have a wire going between the two boxes I wanted to use, but did have power to both boxes. Just connected power and paired the Bluetooth and both switches worked... See more
      This is not listen anywhere in their documentation, but the “power out” wire does not need to be used. I did not have a wire going between the two boxes I wanted to use, but did have power to both boxes. Just connected power and paired the Bluetooth and both switches worked perfect. The “air gap” switch will only work on the switch that has the “power out” wire going up to the fan. But both switches work even tho one (or possibly both) have no physical connection to the fan. This makes installation so much more versatile, I wish they would have incudes that in documentation. Could have been an expensive experiment, but turned out great.

      Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2020
      I love my Modern Forms fan, and it integrates well with both Alexa and Google Home. But: from time to time, the connection with both Alexa and Google is lost, which requires deleting the Modern Forms skill and then re-installing them, and linking them to your Modern Forms... See more
      I love my Modern Forms fan, and it integrates well with both Alexa and Google Home. But: from time to time, the connection with both Alexa and Google is lost, which requires deleting the Modern Forms skill and then re-installing them, and linking them to your Modern Forms account again. No big deal, really, but sometimes it's too much bother (for instance, if I'm getting ready to go to bed and ask Alexa to turn off the fan light and I get a "I can't connect with Modern Forms" message).

      The remote and the wall-switch always work, so if I try a voice command and it's not working, I use one of those. For me, the remote is essential because I'm not always near the wall switch. I also find that I get more precise control over the fan speed with the remote and wall switch than using Alexa. For the money, it has definitely been worth it to me. I've had it for 4 months and so far, no problems.
